<p>Hospital costs in west Germany have risen more than twice as fast as total spending under the country's healthcare reforms, according to the German Health Ministry. Whereas west German healthcare costs were up over 5% in 1994 compared with 1992, the year before the reforms started, hospital expenditure has risen almost 12%. East German hospitals increased spending by 34%, compared with a 28% rise in general health expenditure, as they re-equipped to bring themselves up to western standards.</p>
